      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FIRST FIFTEEN (2) resumed much improved, narrowly beaten from the pace at Sale. Tackled a CL1 at Pakenham following and lacked a change of gears in the run to the line. Has the blinkers on for the first time and maps well in easier. A 4kg claimer is engaged today and that brings her right into it. TIPSY GYPSY (1) resumes and is good on the fresh side. Has jumped out 4x at Flemington, and Brad Rawiller has been with her all along. Won't have to improve much to test. SMASHING RUBY (7) was narrowly beaten at Towong first-up, and there was much to like about her effort after an awkward start. Gets in light again with the 4kg claim, and with the extra fitness, can't be ruled out. POPTHEBUBBLY (3) can build on her Maiden win at Edenhope. Has a 2kg claim today and will position forward from the inside barrier.",
